claim.claim-text:
A saddled vehicle (11) comprising:
a vehicle body frame (12);
a crankcase (29) that defines a crank chamber (41) for housing a counterweight (42a) of a crankshaft (42), the crankcase (29) being coupled to the vehicle body frame (12) to swing about a swing axis (Sx);
a scavenge pump (121) that is fixed to the crankcase (29) and recovers oil in the crank chamber (41);
a scavenge suction passage (124) that is open at the crank chamber (41) and connected to a suction port (122a) of the scavenge pump (121); and
a scavenge discharge port (122b) where the oil is discharged from the scavenge pump (121) into an oil chamber (135) that is separated from the crank chamber (41) and provided in the crankcase (29) below the crank chamber (41), wherein
the oil chamber (135) includes a partition wall (155) that laterally partitions the oil chamber (135) to divide the oil chamber (135) into a first channel space (153) on an upper side and a second channel space (154) on a lower side, and
the partition wall (155) includes at least one communication hole (156) that is continuous from the first channel space (153) to the second channel space (154).
